Kenya's deputy environment minister, Maathai, spearheaded a successful campaign to reduce plastic bag usage by 90%.
The government allocated funds from a plastic bag tax for environmental initiatives.
The United Nations Environment Programme urged Kenya to ban plastic bags, citing health risks.
Despite some opposition, fines were imposed on those involved in plastic bag production.
Similar efforts are being made globally, with San Francisco considering a fee on grocery bags.
Rwanda and Uganda have also taken steps to ban plastic bags due to environmental concerns.
Tanzania is establishing a recycling plant to address the plastic waste issue.
